definition: to go forward/to advance/to go in/to enter/to put in/to submit/to take in/to admit/(math.) base of a number system/classifier for sections in a building or residential compound

sentences.english: Objective To discuss the techniques and methods of rodents killing in in-and-out small - scale ships.
sentences.chinese: 目的探討進出境小型船舶滅鼠的技術和方法。

sentences.english: Loading and unloading inbound and outbound means of transport may be subject to supervision and control of the Customs.
sentences.chinese: 海關可以對進出境運輸工具裝卸貨物實施監裝監卸。

sentences.english: The Customs valuation of inward and outward articles shall be determined by the Customs according to law.
sentences.chinese: 進出境物品的完稅價格，由海關依法確定。

sentences.english: In China, ivories are also listed as prohibited items of entry and exit from the country.
sentences.chinese: 在中國，象牙製品也屬於禁止進出境物品之列。

sentences.english: The belongings of a temporary visitor who is leaving the country should not exceed travel needs.
sentences.chinese: 短期旅客攜帶進出境的行李物品應以旅行需用品爲限。

sentences.english: The dutiable price for inward and outward articles shall be determined by the Customs in accordance with law.
sentences.chinese: 進出境物品的完稅價格，由海關依法確定。
